{% from "hooks/vfs-hints" import vfs_analysis, structural_nav, ssot_reminder, batch_edit_hint %}
{% if tool_name == "Bash" %}
{% for rel in rel_paths %}
{% if bin == "cat" %}
Hint (nyne VFS): Prefer the **Read tool** over `cat` for reading files. Use `Read {{ rel }}@/symbols/{{ FILE_OVERVIEW }}` to see the file's structure with token estimates, then `Read` only the symbol you need. Reserve `cat` for batch reads (brace expansion) and pipelines.
{% elif bin in ["head", "tail"] %}
Hint (nyne VFS): Line offsets are fragile — they shift when the file changes. Use `{{ rel }}@/symbols/{{ FILE_OVERVIEW }}` to find the symbol you're looking for, then read its body directly. Symbol paths are stable across edits.
{% elif bin in ["grep", "rg"] %}
Hint (nyne VFS): Instead of grepping a raw file, read `{{ rel }}@/symbols/{{ FILE_OVERVIEW }}` to locate the symbol containing your pattern, then read its body.
{% elif bin == "wc" %}
Hint (nyne VFS): `{{ rel }}@/symbols/{{ FILE_OVERVIEW }}` includes line counts and token estimates for every symbol. You can assess file size and complexity without reading the file at all.
{% elif bin == "sed" %}
Hint (nyne VFS): Line-range extraction is fragile — lines shift after edits. Use `{{ rel }}@/symbols/{{ FILE_OVERVIEW }}` to identify the symbol at those lines, then read its body. Symbol paths stay valid even when surrounding code changes.
{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}
{% if ssot and rel %}
{{ ssot_reminder(rel) }}
{% endif %}
{% if overview_rel %}
Before modifying symbols in {{ overview_rel }}:
{{ vfs_analysis(file=overview_rel) }}
{% endif %}
{% if tool_name == "Grep" and tool_input.pattern %}
Hint: Prefer these over the built-in Grep tool:
  rg "{{ tool_input.pattern }}" — ripgrep, faster and already on this system
  ast-grep -p '$PATTERN' — structural code search (AST-aware, no false positives)

For symbol-level analysis, use nyne VFS:
{{ vfs_analysis() }}
{% endif %}
{% if tool_name == "Glob" and tool_input.pattern %}
Hint: Prefer these over the built-in Glob tool:
  fd '{{ tool_input.pattern }}' — fast file finder (use -g for glob patterns, regex by default)

For structural navigation, use nyne VFS:
{{ structural_nav() }}
{% endif %}
{% if hints %}
Code analysis hints:
{% for rule_id, group in hints|groupby("rule_id") %}
{% if group|length >= 3 %}
- [{{ group[0].severity }}:{{ rule_id }}] ×{{ group|length }} occurrences
{% else %}
{% for hint in group %}
- [{{ hint.severity }}:{{ hint.rule_id }}] L{{ hint.line_start }}{% if hint.line_end != hint.line_start %}-{{ hint.line_end }}{% endif %}: {{ hint.message }}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
Address all hints unless fixing them is non-trivial (e.g. requires a larger refactor). Briefly note what you fixed.
{% endif %}
{% if diagnostics %}
LSP diagnostics ({{ diagnostics|length }}):
{% for d in diagnostics %}
- L{{ d.line }}:{{ d.col }} [{{ d.severity }}] {{ d.message }}{% if d.code %} ({{ d.code }}){% endif %}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}
